Object.assign(translations.en, {
  articleIntros: {
    'edit-lesson-background-color': "In Edit Lesson, you can freely change the background color of each Activity slide to the color you want. The selected color is applied to the slide in real time.",
    'edit-lesson-preview': "Preview lets you check how a Lesson will look on the teacher and student screens before starting the actual class. Responses are not saved, so you can test freely.",
    'edit-lesson-undo-redo': "In Edit Lesson, you can use **Undo / Redo** when you accidentally make the wrong change while working or want to return to a previous state.",
    'edit-lesson-presentation': "Presentation mode is an offline class mode that lets you teach without an internet connection. It is a presentation-focused mode where the teacher leads the class by showing Lesson content on screen without real-time interaction with students.",
    'edit-lesson-interaction': "Interaction mode is a class mode where students can participate with real-time responses. As the teacher moves through slides, students can join Activities such as Quiz and Discussion directly from their own devices, making it easier to run an interactive class.",
    'edit-lesson-ai-make': "**✦ AI Make** is a feature that automatically creates Activities when you upload a file. Based on class materials such as PDF or PPT files, you can quickly create the Activity type you need, such as a Full Lesson, Quiz, or Discussion, which can greatly reduce class preparation time.\n\nYou can bring in files in two ways: **local file (From File)** and **Google Drive**.",
    'edit-lesson-load-storage': "You can load another Lesson saved in My Storage into the Edit Lesson you are currently working on. You can import an entire Lesson or selectively import only the Activity you want, so you can reuse class content efficiently.\n\nThere are two ways to load a Lesson from My Storage.",
    'edit-lesson-add-activity': "An Activity is a slide-level activity that makes up a Lesson. You can add multiple Activities inside one Lesson to build the class flow.\n\nThere are two ways to add an Activity: **+ Manual** and **✦ AI Make**.",
    'edit-lesson-rename': "A Lesson name is an important identifier for distinguishing classes. Because a newly created Lesson is saved with the default name \"Untitled Lesson\", changing it to a name that clearly describes the class content helps you find the Lesson faster later.\n\nThere are two ways to change a Lesson name.",
    'edit-lesson-create': 'A Lesson is the smallest content unit used to organize a class in LumiTeach. If you create a Lesson before starting a new class, you can set up the class flow in advance.\n\nThere are two main ways to create a Lesson: **create it directly from the Home screen** or **create it during class while in Teaching status**.',
    'edit-lesson-background-image': 'Use a custom image when a solid background color is not enough for the slide. You can upload an image from your device or search for one on the web.',
    'edit-lesson-activity-common-setting': 'Activity Common Setting lets you control options shared by an Activity, such as showing a countdown before the Activity starts and setting a response time limit.',
    'edit-lesson-text-properties': 'Text properties are edited from the toolbar that appears when you select a text object. You can adjust text style, duplicate or delete the object, and change its layer order.',
    "edit-lesson-rewrite": "Rewrite helps you quickly adjust the length, tone, and wording of text in a slide without rewriting it manually.",
    "edit-lesson-add-text-object": "Add Text lets you place an additional text object anywhere on a slide. Use it when you need an extra title, instruction, or explanation outside the slide layout.",
    "edit-lesson-add-shape": "Shape objects help you emphasize an area, separate content visually, or guide the slide flow with arrows and simple graphic elements.",
    "edit-lesson-upload-image": "Use Add Image when you need to place an image object on a slide. You can add an image from a local file or through web search.",
    "edit-lesson-image-properties": "After adding an image, use the properties toolbar at the top to adjust how the image appears and how it is arranged with other objects on the slide.",
    "edit-lesson-webviewer": "Use Web Viewer when you want to provide a web page in a Lesson as a link students can open during class.",
  }
});
Object.assign(translations.en.articleBodies, {
    'edit-lesson-background-color': [
      "On the Edit Lesson screen, click the **✏️ (pencil) icon** in the right toolbar. The **Background Color** panel opens on the right.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-background-color/01.png|Background Color panel in the right toolbar]]\n\n### Select a color\n\nChoose the color you want in the **color picker**.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-background-color/02.png|Background Color color picker]]\n\n- **Color gradient area**: Click or drag to adjust the brightness and saturation of the color.\n- **Rainbow slider**: Drag left or right to change the Hue.\n- **HEX code input**: Enter a HEX color code directly in the text field at the bottom. Example: `#427bff`\n- **Eyedropper icon**: Pick a specific color from the screen and apply it as the background color.\n\nWhen you select a color, it is applied to the slide background immediately.",
      "- The same panel also has a **Background Image** section at the bottom. Use this section if you want to set the background as an image instead of a solid color. See 11. Add and change a background image.\n- Background color settings are applied per slide. You can set a different background color for each slide."
    ],
    'edit-lesson-preview': [
      "Click the **Preview 👁** button at the top center of the Edit Lesson screen. It is located to the right of the Undo / Redo icons and to the left of the Self Study button.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-preview/01.png|Preview button at the top of the Edit Lesson screen]]",
      "When you enter the Preview screen, the following notice appears at the top.\n\n> **\"This is a preview screen. Your responses will not be saved.\"**\n> Because this is a preview screen, entered responses are not saved.\n\nThe screen is divided into two areas.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-preview/02.png|Presentation Screen and Audience Screen in Preview]]\n\n- **Presentation Screen** (left): The screen the teacher sees during class. It shows the actual class UI, including Access Code, Instructor View, End Lesson, and slide navigation.\n- **Audience Screen** (right): The screen shown on the student device. You can check how the content appears from the student perspective.",
      "Use the **View Mobile** toggle at the bottom-right of the Preview screen to switch the student screen to a mobile layout.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-preview/03.png|Check mobile layout with the View Mobile toggle]]\n\n- **Toggle OFF**: Audience Screen appears in a PC / tablet screen ratio.\n- **Toggle ON**: Audience Screen switches to a vertical mobile screen ratio. This is useful when checking the screen students will see on smartphones.\n\nClick the **X** button in the upper-right corner to close Preview and return to the Edit Lesson screen."
    ],
    'edit-lesson-undo-redo': [
      "The **← (Undo)** and **→ (Redo)** icons are located side by side at the top center of the Edit Lesson screen. You can find them to the left of the Preview, Self Study, and Start Teaching buttons.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-undo-redo/01.png|Undo and Redo buttons at the top of the Edit Lesson screen]]\n\n- **← Undo**: Cancels the previous action and returns to the earlier state.\n- **→ Redo**: Runs the action you canceled again.",
      "- Undo / Redo remembers up to **50 actions**. Actions older than the 50-action limit cannot be restored.\n- If you **leave the Edit Lesson screen and enter again**, the Undo / Redo history is reset. Check your work carefully before moving to another page."
    ],
    'edit-lesson-presentation': [
      "Click the **∨** button next to **Start Teaching** in the upper-right corner of the Edit Lesson screen. A class mode dropdown appears. Select **Presentation**.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-presentation/01.png|Select Presentation from the Start Teaching dropdown]]\n\n- **Interaction**: An interaction-focused class mode that receives student responses in real time.\n- **Presentation**: An offline class mode for presenting a Lesson without an internet connection.\n- **Battle Mode**: A battle-style class mode that can only run in an online environment.\n\nWhen you select **Presentation**, you move directly to the class screen without Access Type settings or student participation.",
      "When you enter Presentation mode, the **Lesson View** screen appears.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-presentation/02.png|Presentation Lesson View screen]]\n\n- **Top center — Lesson View**: Indicates that you are currently teaching in Presentation mode.\n- **Top right — End Lesson**: Ends the class.\n- **Left and right arrows (◀ ▶)**: Move to the previous or next slide. You can also use the keyboard arrow keys.\n- **Bottom slide position, such as 1/5**: Shows the current position within the full slide set.\n\n> **Difference from Interaction mode**: Presentation mode does not show Access Code, Instructor View, or student count. It is operated as a teacher-only screen for presenting content."
    ],
    'edit-lesson-interaction': [
      "Click the **∨** button next to **Start Teaching** in the upper-right corner of the Edit Lesson screen. A class mode dropdown appears. Select **Interaction**.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-interaction/01.png|Select Interaction from the Start Teaching dropdown]]\n\n- **Interaction**: An online class mode suited for receiving student responses.\n- **Presentation**: An offline mode that can be used without an internet connection.\n- **Battle Mode**: A battle-style class mode that can only run in an online environment.",
      "In the **Choose Access Type** popup, select who can join the class.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-interaction/02.png|Choose Access Type popup]]\n\n- **Public Link (Guest Access)**: Anyone who knows the link or Access Code can join. If you have not assigned a Class separately, choose this option.\n- **Class Only (Private Access)**: Only students assigned to a specific Class can join.\n\nAfter selecting an option, click **Assign**.\n\n### When selecting Class Only — assign a class\n\nIf you select Class Only, the **Choose a class** popup appears next. Set the class that will participate.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-interaction/03.png|Class assignment popup after selecting Class Only]]\n\n- **Year**: Select the school year, such as 2026.\n- **School**: Select the school.\n- **Grade**: Select the grade.\n- **Class Name** (required): Select the specific class.\n\nAfter completing the settings, click **Apply**.",
      "When setup is complete, the Interaction class screen opens.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-interaction/04.png|Interaction class screen]]\n\n- **Upper left — Access Code**: The code students enter when they access LumiTeach. Share this code with students so they can join the class.\n- **Upper right — Instructor View**: Opens the instructor view, where teachers can check slide previews, timers, and student questions at a glance.\n- **Upper right — End Lesson**: Ends the class.\n- **Bottom slide navigation (< 1/5 >)**: Moves to the previous or next slide.\n- **Bottom right — number of students**: Shows the number of students currently participating in the class in real time."
    ],
    'edit-lesson-ai-make': [
      "### Step 1. Start AI Make\n\nOn the Edit Lesson screen, click **✦ AI Make**. If the screen is empty and has no Activity yet, click the **✦ AI Make** button in the center. If Activities already exist, click **✦ AI Make** in the upper-left corner.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-ai-make/01.png|AI Make button on the Edit Lesson screen]]\n\n### Step 2. Upload a file\n\nWhen the **Make with AI** popup opens, the **From File** tab is selected by default. Click the upload area or click **Upload file** to choose a file.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-ai-make/02.png|From File tab in the Make with AI popup]]\n\n- Supported file format: **pdf, doc, docx, ppt, pptx**\n- File limit: 1 file, up to 50 MB\n\nAfter you select a file, loading starts with the \"Checking file type...\" message.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-ai-make/04.png|Checking file type state after uploading a file]]\n\n### Step 3. Select pages\n\nWhen file analysis is complete, page previews of the document appear. Select the pages that AI should use as reference.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-ai-make/05.png|Page previews after file analysis]]\n\n- You can select up to **30 pages** at a time.\n- After selecting pages, click **Import N Pages**.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-ai-make/05.png|Import after selecting pages for AI reference]]\n\n### Step 4. Set Required information\n\nIn **Activity Composition**, choose the Activity type to generate.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-ai-make/06.png|Select Activity Composition]]\n\n- **Full Lesson**: Builds the full class flow based on the uploaded material.\n- **Quiz**: Creates a Quiz Activity for checking student understanding.\n- **Discussion**: Creates a discussion-based Activity that encourages different opinions.\n\nIn **Number of activities to Generate**, set how many Activities to create. For Full Lesson, you can adjust the number within the **5 to 20** range.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-ai-make/13.png|Set Number of activities to Generate]]\n\n### Step 5. Set Optional options\n\nYou can configure additional options in the **Optional** section.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-ai-make/07.png|Optional settings area]]\n\n- **Preference**: Set Grade, Subject, and Language.\n- **Difficulty**: Choose Auto, Basic, Intermediate, or Advanced.\n- **Topic**: Enter an optional topic within 200 characters to guide the generation direction.\n\nAfter completing the settings, click **Generate**.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-ai-make/14.png|Run the Generate button]]\n\n### Step 6. Complete generation\n\nThe \"**AI is Generating...**\" screen appears while AI creates the Activities. When generation is complete, the Activities are automatically added to Edit Lesson.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-ai-make/08.png|AI is Generating screen]]\n\nIf you click **Cancel Generating** during generation, a cancellation confirmation popup appears.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-ai-make/08.png|Cancel Generating button]]\n\n> **\"Used AI credits are non-refundable. Are you sure you want to cancel?\"**\n> - **Keep**: Continue generation.\n> - **Cancel**: Stop generation.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-ai-make/16.png|AI generation cancellation confirmation popup]]\n\n⚠️ **AI credits are not refunded even if you cancel.** Credits used up to the cancellation point are treated as already consumed. Once generation has started, it is generally recommended to let it finish.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-ai-make/09.png|Activities added after AI generation is complete]]\n\nEven if you are not satisfied with the generated Activities, you can edit them directly at any time. (Service Tip: \"Not satisfied with the AI-generated options? You can click to edit them anytime!\")\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-ai-make/09.png|Guide to editing AI-generated results]]",
      "In the **Make with AI** popup, select the **Google Drive** tab. When the **Select a file** window opens, choose the file you want from My Drive.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-ai-make/10.png|Select a file from the Google Drive tab]]\n\n- Google Drive also supports additional formats: **pdf, doc, docx, ppt, pptx, odt, rtf, odp, txt**\n- After you select a file, the conversion progress appears as \"Converting file N%...\". When conversion is complete, you move to the page preview screen.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-ai-make/11.png|Google Drive file conversion progress]]\n\nAfter that, **Steps 4 to 6** are the same as the local file method.\n\n> ⚠️ AI Make **deducts AI credits**. Before generating, check the \"AI credits will be deducted.\" notice at the bottom."
    ],
  'edit-lesson-load-storage': [
    "While working on the Edit Lesson screen, you can bring in content from My Storage directly.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-load-storage/01.png|Move to the My Storage tab from Edit Lesson]]\n\n- Enter the Edit Lesson screen.\n- Click the **+ Manual** button in the upper-left corner or in the center of the screen.\n- When the **Create Manually** popup opens, click the **My Storage** tab at the top.\n- The folders and Lessons saved in My Storage are displayed. Select the Lesson you want.\n- Select the Activity Slide to import from the Lesson.\n- To import all Activities, click the **Select All Activity** checkbox.\n- Click **Import** to add the selected Activity to the current Lesson.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-load-storage/02.png|Select a Lesson from My Storage]]\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-load-storage/03.png|Import the selected Activity with Import]]",
    "You can also load another Lesson from My Storage while a class is in progress. This is useful when you need to add content on the spot according to the class flow.\n\n- Click **Load** at the top of the Teaching screen.\n- The **Load** popup opens. The folder structure in My Storage appears in the left panel.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-load-storage/04.png|Load popup on the Teaching screen]]\n\n- **My Storage**: Full folder list, such as the third folder, first folder, and fourth folder\n- **Favorites**: Folders and Lessons added to Favorites\n- In the right panel, choose the view you want from the **All** tab (folders + all Lessons) or the **Lessons** tab (Lesson-only filter).\n- Use the **Search** field at the top to quickly search for a specific Lesson.\n- Select the folder or Lesson you want, then click **Import** in the lower-right corner to load it into the current class.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-load-storage/05.png|Select a Lesson during Teaching and import it]]"
  ],
  'edit-lesson-add-activity': [
    "If there is no Activity on the Edit Lesson screen, the message \"Click the button to create your first activity.\" appears in the center of the screen with the **+ Manual** and **✦ AI Make** buttons. To directly choose and add an Activity, click **+ Manual**. If an Activity already exists, click **+ Manual** in the upper-left corner.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-add-activity/01.png|+ Manual button on the Edit Lesson screen]]\n\nThe **Create Manually** popup opens. At the top, there are **Add** and **My Storage** tabs, and you can choose the Activity type you want from the category list on the left.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-add-activity/02.png|Activity categories in the Create Manually popup]]\n\nThe categories are as follows.\n\n- **General**: Basic slide layouts such as text and image (Text Only, Text & Text, Image, Text Top, Image Middle, Image Top, Image Left, Image Right, Blank)\n- **Embed**: Insert external content such as web pages, YouTube, and documents\n- **Quiz**: Quiz Activity types such as True or False, Multiple Choice, and Short Answer\n- **Discussion**: Discussion Activity types such as Agree/Disagree and Vote\n- **Idea Board**: Brainstorming and Whiteboard\n- **Games**: Game-based Activities\n\nAfter selecting the category you want, click a detailed Activity type on the right to add it immediately.\n\nOnce the Activity is added, you can edit the content directly on the Edit Lesson screen. You can check the Activity list in the left slide panel, and adjust detailed options such as Background Color, Common Setting (such as 3 Second's Countdown), and Result form (such as Bar Chart and Bubble) in the right settings panel.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-add-activity/03.png|Edit Lesson editing screen after adding an Activity]]",
    "Click **✦ AI Make** to let AI automatically create an Activity. Enter a topic or keyword, and AI suggests an appropriate Activity structure. Use this when you want to create class content quickly."
  ],
  'edit-lesson-rename': [
    "At the top of the Edit Lesson screen, the current Lesson name appears as a text field. Click the Lesson name to switch it into an editable input state. Enter the desired name, then press **Enter** to save it automatically. You can check the save status with the cloud icon on the right.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-rename/01.png|Lesson name input area at the top of the Edit Lesson screen]]\n\n- Click the Lesson name at the top of the Edit Lesson screen.\n- Change it to the desired name.\n- Press **Enter** to save.",
    "On the Lessons screen in My Storage, click the **⋮ (More)** button at the upper-right of each Lesson card to open the dropdown menu.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-rename/02.png|More menu on a Lesson card in My Storage]]\n\n- The menu shows various options, including starting a class (Interaction, Presentation, Battle Mode), Self Study (Individual, Challenge, Flash Card), and additional menu items (Favorites, Edit Lesson, **Rename**, Duplicate, Move, Publish).\n- Click **Rename**.\n\nWhen you click **Rename**, the name area at the bottom of the Lesson card changes into an editable text field. Enter the desired Lesson name, then press **Enter** to save.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-rename/03.png|Editing the name at the bottom of a Lesson card]]\n\n- Go to My Storage → Lessons.\n- Click the **⋮** button on the Lesson card you want to rename.\n- Click **Rename** from the dropdown menu.\n- Enter the new Lesson name, then press **Enter** to save."
  ],
  'edit-lesson-create': [
    'When you access LumiTeach, the **Create** button and **Start Teaching** button appear in the top navigation bar. To create a new Lesson, click **Create** at the top.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-create/01.png|Create button at the top of the Home screen]]\n\nClicking **Create** takes you to the Edit Lesson screen. On first entry, the screen starts empty without any Activity. In the center, the message "Click the button to create the first activity." appears with two buttons: **+ Manual** and **✦ AI Make**.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-create/02.png|+ Manual and AI Make buttons on the empty Edit Lesson screen]]\n\n- **+ Manual**: Manually select an Activity type and add it yourself.\n- **✦ AI Make**: Let AI automatically generate an Activity.\n\nAdd Activity in the way you prefer to build the Lesson.',
    'You can also create a new Lesson while a class is already in progress. In this case, the current class is ended and a new Lesson is created next.\n\nClick **Start Teaching** at the top of the Home screen to open the dropdown menu. Select a class mode.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-create/03.png|Select a class mode from the Start Teaching dropdown]]\n\n- **Interaction**: A real-time class mode focused on interaction with students.\n- **Presentation**: A class mode where the teacher presents content.\n\nAfter selecting a class mode, the **Choose Access Type** popup appears. Set the class participation range.\n\n- **Public Link (Guest Access)**: A public class that anyone with the link can join.\n- **Class Only (Private Access)**: A private class that only students assigned to a specific Class can join.\n\nIf you have not assigned a Class separately, select **Public Link**. Lesson creation works the same way regardless of which option you choose. After completing the setting, click **Assign**.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-create/04.png|Choose Access Type popup]]\n\nWhen you enter the Teaching screen, the **Create** and **Load** buttons, Access Code, and the **End Lesson** button in the upper-right corner are displayed. Click **Create** at the top, and a popup appears explaining that the current class will end. Click **Confirm** to end the current class and move to the Edit Lesson screen for creating a new Lesson.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-create/05.png|Create a new Lesson from the Teaching screen]]'
  ],
    'edit-lesson-background-image': [
      'On the Edit Lesson screen, click the **✏️ (pencil) icon** in the right toolbar. In the **Background Image** section at the bottom of the **Background Color** panel, click **Upload file**.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-background-image/01.png|How to set a background image]]\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-background-image/02.png|How to set a background image]]',
      'The **Upload Image** pop-up opens. There are two ways to add an image.\n\n### Method 1. From File (local file)\n\nIn the **From File** tab, upload an image saved on your device.\n\n- **Drag and drop** an image into the upload area, or click **Upload file** to select a file.\n\n- Supported formats: **png, jpg, jpeg, webp**\n\n- File limit: 1 file, up to **20 MB**\n\n### Method 2. Search from web\n\nIn the **Search from web** tab, search by keyword and bring in an image directly.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-background-image/03.png|Upload an image]]',
      'After selecting a file, the image preview screen appears. Check the image, then click **Apply** in the lower-right corner to apply it as the slide background.\n\nAfter it is applied, the uploaded file name appears in the **Background Image** section of the right panel. Click the **X** button on the right to remove the background image and return to the default background.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-background-image/04.png|Apply the image]]'
    ],
    'edit-lesson-activity-common-setting': [
      '### 3 Second\'s Countdown\n\nSet whether to show a 3-second countdown before the Activity starts.\n\n- **Toggle ON**: When the Activity starts, the screen shows a 3, 2, 1 countdown before the Activity proceeds.\n\n- **Toggle OFF**: The Activity starts immediately without a countdown.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-activity-common-setting/01.png|Common Setting]]',
      'Set the time limit for the Activity.\n\n- **Toggle ON**: You can enter the time limit in seconds. You can enter up to **300 seconds**.\n\n- If no value is entered, the warning message **"Please set the time."** appears in red. You must enter a time before saving.\n\n- **Toggle OFF**: The Activity runs without a time limit.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-activity-common-setting/02.png|Time Limit]]'
    ],
    'edit-lesson-text-properties': [
      '[[image:edit-lesson-text-properties/01.png|Top toolbar shown when a text object is selected]]\n\nWhen you click a text object in Edit Lesson, the text properties toolbar appears at the top. From this toolbar, you can change the basic text style and object controls together.\n\nThe main functions are as follows.\n\n- **Font**: Select the font to apply to the text object.\n\n- **Size**: Adjust the font size with the `- / +` buttons or by entering a number.\n\n- **Bold / Italic / Underline / Color**: Change the weight, slant, underline, and text color.\n\n- **Alignment**: Change the text alignment.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-text-properties/04.png|Text alignment options]]\n\nIn the alignment menu, you can align text to the left, center, or right. Use this when a sentence is long or when you separate a title and description within a slide.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-text-properties/02.png|Text layer order options]]\n\nWhen several objects overlap, use the layer menu to move the text forward or backward.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-text-properties/03.png|Text object duplicate and delete options]]\n\nUse the duplicate and delete buttons on the right to quickly duplicate or remove the text object.',
      'Check the following when changing text properties.\n\n- **Font changes** are applied to the entire text object. Changing the font for only part of the selected text is not supported.\n\n- **Font size** can be adjusted with the buttons, or you can click the number field and enter the value you want.\n\n- If the text object is hidden behind an image or shape, adjust the layer order.\n\n- A duplicated text object may be created on top of the original, so check its position after duplicating it.'
    ],
    "edit-lesson-rewrite": [
              "Rewrite is a feature where AI automatically refines text objects inside a slide. Without rewriting the text manually, you can quickly change the sentence length, tone, and style of expression.\n\nThe flow is as follows.\n\n- In Edit Lesson, click the text object you want to edit.\n\n- Click the **Rewrite** icon in the top toolbar.\n\n- Choose the option you want from the conversion options shown in the dropdown.\n\n- After AI transforms the text, review the result and adjust it again to fit the purpose of the class.",
              "Rewrite options are used to quickly change text to fit the purpose of the class.\n\nFor example, you can shorten a long sentence, change it into easier wording, or refine it into a tone that feels more familiar to students.\n\n> The screenshots currently in the local image folder are closer to the font selection dropdown than the Rewrite menu, so no incorrect image has been added to this page. When a Rewrite menu screenshot is added, it would be best to place it above the relevant paragraph."
    ],
    "edit-lesson-add-text-object": [
              "[[image:edit-lesson-add-text-object/04.png|Add Text button in the right toolbar]]\n\nOn the Edit Lesson screen, click the **T (Add Text)** button in the right toolbar.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-add-text-object/01.png|Add Text panel]]\n\nThe **Add Text** panel opens on the right, and you can choose one of two text types. Even if the slide already has text, you can add a separate text object to add a title, instruction, or supporting explanation.",
              "[[image:edit-lesson-add-text-object/02.png|Add a Heading text object]]\n\n### Heading\n\nThis is a large, bold text object. It is suitable for content that should be noticed first, such as the slide topic, a question, or an emphasized phrase. The default font size is **48**.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-add-text-object/03.png|Add a Body text object]]\n\n### Body text\n\nThis is a text object with a standard body text size. Use it to add explanations, instructions, or supporting information. The default font size is **20**.",
              "When you click the type you want, a text object is added to the center of the slide with the **Enter Directly** guide text.\n\nAfter adding it, you can continue with the following actions.\n\n- Click the object and enter the text you want directly.\n\n- Adjust the font, size, color, and alignment from the top toolbar.\n\n- Drag it to the desired position within the slide.\n\n- Duplicate or delete it if needed."
    ],
    "edit-lesson-add-shape": [
              "[[image:edit-lesson-add-shape/01.png|Add Shape button in the right toolbar]]\n\nOn the Edit Lesson screen, click the **Add Shape** button in the right toolbar.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-add-shape/02.png|Add Shape panel]]\n\nWhen the **Add Shape** panel opens, select the shape you want. Shapes can be used to create emphasis areas, add visual dividers, or guide the flow with arrows.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-add-shape/03.png|Shape added to the slide]]\n\nWhen you click a shape, a selection box appears on the slide and the shape properties toolbar appears at the top.",
              "A total of **12** shapes are provided.\n\n**9 basic shapes**\n\n- 3 circle types: circle / horizontal oval / vertical oval\n\n- 3 rectangle types: square / horizontal rectangle / vertical rectangle\n\n- 3 triangle types: regular triangle / low triangle / narrow tall triangle\n\n**3 arrow types**\n\n- Solid arrow\n\n- Dotted arrow\n\n- Thin dotted arrow\n\nAfter selecting a shape, drag the resize handles to change its size and move it to the desired position within the slide.",
              "[[image:edit-lesson-add-shape/05.png|Change shape color]]\n\nClick the color button in the shape properties toolbar to open the color picker. You can change the shape color using the color gradient area or a HEX code.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-add-shape/04.png|Change shape opacity]]\n\nIn **Opacity**, adjust the transparency of the shape. When creating an emphasis area over a background image, lowering the opacity helps keep the content visible.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-add-shape/06.png|Change shape corner rounding]]\n\nIn **Corner rounded**, adjust how rounded the corners are. Use this when you want to turn a rectangle shape into a softer box.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-add-shape/07.png|Shape alignment options]]\n\nIn the alignment menu, you can align the shape to the left, center, right, top, middle, or bottom of the slide.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-add-shape/13.png|Shape layer order options]]\n\nIn the layer menu, move the shape forward or backward to adjust the order of overlapping objects.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-add-shape/17.png|Shape duplicate button]]\n\nClick **Duplicate** to duplicate the same shape.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-add-shape/18.png|Shape delete button]]\n\nClick **Delete** to delete the selected shape."
    ],
    "edit-lesson-upload-image": [
              "[[image:edit-lesson-upload-image/01.png|Add Image button in the right toolbar]]\n\nOn the Edit Lesson screen, click the **Add Image** button in the right toolbar.\n\nThe **Upload Image** popup opens, and you can choose how to add an image.\n\n- **From File**: Upload an image saved locally.\n\n- **Search from web**: Search for a web image or bring it in by URL.",
              "[[image:edit-lesson-upload-image/02.png|From File upload area]]\n\nIn the **From File** tab, upload an image saved locally.\n\n- Drag and drop an image into the upload area, or click **Upload file** to select a file.\n\n- Supported formats: **png, jpg, jpeg, webp**\n\n- File limit: 1 file, up to **20 MB**\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-upload-image/03.png|Uploaded image preview]]\n\nAfter uploading, a preview screen appears. Check the image and click **Apply** to add it to the slide.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-upload-image/04.png|Image object added to the slide]]\n\nThe added image can be selected, moved, and resized on the slide.",
              "[[image:edit-lesson-upload-image/07.png|Search from web tab]]\n\nIn the **Search from web** tab, you can search for and bring in web images.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-upload-image/08.png|Enter a web image search keyword]]\n\n- **Enter URL**: Paste an image URL directly to bring it in.\n\n- **Keyword search**: Enter a search term to display related images in a grid.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-upload-image/09.png|Web image search results]]\n\nSelect the image you want from the search results.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-upload-image/10.png|Web search image added to the slide]]\n\nAfter the selected image is added to the slide, you can adjust its position and size.",
              "After adding an image, check the **Change image object properties** document for opacity, corner rounding, alignment, layer order, duplication, and deletion.\n\nThis page covers only how to bring an image into a slide."
    ],
    "edit-lesson-image-properties": [
              "[[image:edit-lesson-image-properties/01.png|Opacity panel]]\n\nClick **Opacity** to open the opacity adjustment panel.\n\n- Drag the slider left or right, or enter a % value directly.\n\n- Range: **0 to 100%**.\n\n- **100%** means fully opaque, and **0%** means fully transparent.",
              "[[image:edit-lesson-image-properties/02.png|Corner rounded panel]]\n\nClick **Corner rounded** to open the corner rounding panel.\n\n- Use the slider to adjust how rounded the corners are.\n\n- **0%** means square corners.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-image-properties/03.png|Corner rounded result]]\n\nIncreasing the rounding value makes the image corners rounded. Use this when you need a softer look, such as for card-style images or profile images.",
              "[[image:edit-lesson-image-properties/04.png|Image alignment options]]\n\nClick the alignment button to show 6 alignment options. Align the image object to a reference position within the slide.\n\n- **Align Left**: Align to the left\n\n- **Align Center**: Align to the horizontal center\n\n- **Align Right**: Align to the right\n\n- **Align Top**: Align to the top\n\n- **Align Middle**: Align to the vertical middle\n\n- **Align Bottom**: Align to the bottom",
              "[[image:edit-lesson-image-properties/05.png|Image layer order options]]\n\nClick the layer button to adjust the front-back order of the object. Use this when several images, text objects, or shapes overlap.\n\n- **Bring to Front**: Move to the very front\n\n- **Bring Forward**: Move one step forward\n\n- **Send Backward**: Move one step backward\n\n- **Send to Back**: Move to the very back",
              "[[image:edit-lesson-image-properties/06.png|Image duplicate button]]\n\nClick **Duplicate** to duplicate the image object with the same properties. The duplicated object may be created on top of the original, so check its position.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-image-properties/07.png|Image delete button]]\n\nClick **Delete** to delete the selected image object."
    ],
    "edit-lesson-webviewer": [
              "[[image:edit-lesson-webviewer/01.png|Add Web Viewer Activity screen]]\n\nIn Edit Lesson, select **+ Manual** → **Embed** category → **Web Viewer** to add the Activity.\n\nWhen the Activity is added, the **Add web link** guide text appears in the center of the slide, and the Web link input area appears in the right panel.",
              "[[image:edit-lesson-webviewer/02.png|Completed Web link input screen]]\n\nEnter the URL of the web page you want to show in the **Web link** input field in the right panel.\n\n- When you enter a valid URL, the link appears on the slide and the **Well Done!** confirmation message appears in the panel.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-webviewer/11.png|Web link input error state]]\n\nIf the URL format is invalid or the link is empty, the input field shows a warning state. In this case, the link may not appear correctly on the student screen, so check the URL again.\n\n> If the message **This content cannot be embedded. The attached link will be provided.** appears, the web page cannot be embedded directly inside the slide and will be provided as a link button instead.",
              "[[image:edit-lesson-webviewer/07.png|Web Viewer Background Color setting screen]]\n\nIn the **Background Color** area at the top of the right panel, you can change the background color of the Web Viewer slide. Set it with the color picker or by entering a HEX code directly.",
              "[[image:edit-lesson-webviewer/03.png|Web Viewer Preview screen]]\n\nWhen you check it in **Preview**, the entered URL appears as a link button on the **Audience Screen** that students see. Students can click the button to move to the web page.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-webviewer/04.png|Web Viewer mobile Preview screen]]\n\nTurn on the **View Mobile** toggle to preview how the screen will appear to students on mobile devices."
    ],
  
    "edit-lesson-youtube": [
              "[[image:edit-lesson-youtube/01.png|Youtube Activity add screen]]\n\nIn Edit Lesson, select **+ Manual** → **Embed** category → **Youtube** to add the Activity.",
              "[[image:edit-lesson-youtube/02.png|Youtube Link entered screen]]\n\nAfter the Youtube Activity is added, the slide shows the YouTube icon in the center with the **Add Youtube link** guidance. In the right panel, enter the YouTube video URL you want to insert in the **Youtube Link** input field.\n\n- When you enter a valid YouTube URL, the video thumbnail, title, and play button appear on the slide, and the panel shows the confirmation state.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-youtube/03.png|Youtube Link required state]]\n\nIf the link is empty or invalid, the **Please enter the link** message appears. In this case, enter the YouTube URL again first.",
              "When you move to this slide in the Teaching screen, the inserted YouTube video appears. Click the play button to play the video directly.\n\nYou can click the link icon at the lower-left of the slide to open the original YouTube page.",
              "In the **Background Color** area at the top of the right panel, you can change the slide background color."
    ]});

