Object.assign(translations.en.articleBodies, {
      "edit-lesson-quiz-matching": [
            "[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-matching/01.png|Matching editing screen]]\n\nAfter clicking **+ Manual**, select **Quiz → Matching** in the **Create Manually** popup to add the Activity.\n\nThe slide is structured so that items on the left (1, 2, 3, 4...) are connected by lines to items on the right (A, B, C, D...).\n\n### Layout Type\n\nIn **Layout Type** in the right panel, choose how items are displayed.\n\n- **Text-Based**: Enter left and right items as text. During class, students connect the text items with lines.\n\n- **Image-Based**: Upload images for the left and right items. During class, students connect the image cards with lines.\n\nIn the Edit Lesson preview, the correct connection lines appear crossed so you can check the matching structure.\n\n### Setting options (right panel)\n\n**Common Setting**\n\n- **3 Second's Countdown**: Turn on the toggle to run a 3-second countdown before the question appears.\n\n**Result form**\n\n- **Bar Chart**: Aggregates the number of correct/incorrect responses as a bar chart.",
            "[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-matching/02.png|Text-Based Matching class start screen]]\n\nOn the class screen, the question title and left/right items are displayed.\n\n- **Text-Based**: Text items numbered 1-4 appear on the left, and description items labeled A-D appear on the right.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-matching/07.png|Image-Based Matching class start screen]]\n\n- **Image-Based**: Numbered image cards appear on the left, and alphabet-labeled image cards appear on the right.\n\nClick **Let's Begin** to start student responses.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-matching/10.png|Matching submission status panel]]\n\nClick **Instructor View** to open the **Submitted / Not Submitted** panel. Turn on the **Show Correct/Incorrect** toggle to check each student's correct/incorrect status by color.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-matching/12.png|Image-Based Matching result screen]]\n\nAfter closing responses, the result screen shows students' matching status, and you can reveal the correct connection lines with **See Answer**.",
            "[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-matching/13.png|Student connected Text-Based Matching screen]]\n\nOn the student screen, left/right items and connection points (round buttons) next to each item are displayed. The student taps a point on a left item and drags to a point on a right item to draw a connection line. Each item is distinguished by color.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-matching/16.png|Student connected Image-Based Matching screen]]\n\nAfter connecting all items, press **Submit** at the bottom to submit.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-matching/18.png|Matching answer reveal screen]]\n\nWhen the teacher reveals the answer with **See Answer**, the student screen shows **Correct** or **Wrong** feedback with the correct connection lines.\n\n- **Image-Based** answer screen: Correctly matched image pairs are displayed with borders.\n\n- **Text-Based** answer screen: Correct connection lines are displayed in color so students can check the correct matching."
      ]
});
