Object.assign(translations.en.articleBodies, {
      "edit-lesson-quiz-sequencing": [
            "[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-sequencing/01.png|Sequencing Image-Based editing screen]]\n\nAfter clicking **+ Manual**, select **Quiz → Sequencing** in the **Create Manually** popup to add the Activity.\n\n### Layout Type\n\nIn **Layout Type** in the right panel, choose how items are displayed.\n\n- **Image-Based**: Upload an image for each item. Numbered sequence slots (1→2→3...) and image cards appear on the slide.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-sequencing/02.png|Sequencing Text-Based editing screen]]\n\n- **Text-Based**: Enter the text items to arrange in order. On the student screen, students drag the text items into the sequence slots.\n\n### Setting options (right panel)\n\n**Common Setting**\n\n- **3 Second's Countdown**: Turn on the toggle to run a 3-second countdown before the question appears.\n\n**Result form**\n\n- **Bar Chart**: Displays the number of Correct / Wrong responses as a bar chart.\n\n**Time Limit**\n\n- Turn on the toggle to set the student response time limit in seconds.",
            "[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-sequencing/11.png|Image-Based Sequencing class start screen]]\n\n### Image-Based\n\nAt the top of the class screen, numbered empty slots (1→2→3→4→5) are displayed, and shuffled image cards are listed at the bottom.\n\nClick **Let's Begin** to start student responses. Click **Instructor View** to open the **Submitted / Not Submitted** panel. When **Show Correct/Incorrect** is off, you can check only whether students submitted; when it is on, you can also check correct/incorrect status.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-sequencing/17.png|Image-Based Sequencing result Bar Chart]]\n\nAfter closing responses, check the result screen with **View Result**. On the result screen, the number of Correct / Wrong responses is displayed as a graph.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-sequencing/19.png|Text-Based Sequencing class start screen]]\n\n### Text-Based\n\nIn the Text-Based layout, sequence slots appear on the left and a list of text items appears on the right. Students need to place the text items in the correct order.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-sequencing/22.png|Text-Based Sequencing answer reveal screen]]\n\nClick **See Answer** to reveal the correct order.",
            "[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-sequencing/24.png|Image-Based Sequencing question on the student screen]]\n\n### Image-Based\n\nNumbered slots (1→2→3...) are displayed at the top, and shuffled image cards are displayed at the bottom. Following the guide text **Drag & drop options to the deck in order** at the lower right, students drag the bottom cards into the top slots in order.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-sequencing/26.png|Image-Based Sequencing ready-to-submit state]]\n\nWhen all slots are filled, the **Submit** button becomes active in blue.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-sequencing/23.png|Image-Based Sequencing answer feedback screen]]\n\nWhen the teacher reveals the correct answer, the student screen shows Correct / Wrong feedback together with the correct order.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-sequencing/29.png|Text-Based Sequencing question on the student screen]]\n\n### Text-Based\n\nNumbered slots are displayed on the left, and a list of text items is displayed on the right. Students drag items into the left slots in order.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-sequencing/33.png|Text-Based Sequencing ready-to-submit state]]\n\nWhen all items are placed, the **Submit** button becomes active.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-sequencing/38.png|Text-Based Sequencing answer feedback screen]]\n\nAfter the correct answer is revealed, the correct text order is displayed so students can compare it with their own arrangement."
      ]
});
