Object.assign(translations.en.articleBodies, {
      "edit-lesson-quiz-sorting": [
            "[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-sorting/01.png|Sorting Image-Based editing screen]]\n\nAfter clicking **+ Manual**, select **Quiz → Sorting** in the **Create Manually** popup to add the Activity.\n\nGroup boxes (Group A, Group B...) are placed at the top of the slide, and the items to classify are listed at the bottom.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-sorting/05.png|Image-Based Sorting correct placement screen]]\n\nIn Image-Based, drag images into each group to configure the correct classification. During class, students place images into groups in the same way.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-sorting/08.png|Sorting Text-Based editing screen]]\n\n### Layout Type\n\nIn **Layout Type** in the right panel, choose how items are displayed.\n\n- **Image-Based**: Drag images into groups to classify them.\n\n- **Text-Based**: Drag text items into groups to classify them.\n\n### Setting options (right panel)\n\n**Common Setting**\n\n- **3 Second's Countdown**: Turn on the toggle to run a 3-second countdown before the question appears.\n\n**Result form**\n\n- **Bar Chart**: Displays the number of Correct / Wrong responses as a bar chart.",
            "[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-sorting/09.png|Image-Based Sorting class start screen]]\n\n### Image-Based\n\nOn the class screen, group boxes such as Animal and Plant appear at the top, and image cards to classify are listed at the bottom. The guide text **Sort options by drag & drop** appears inside each box.\n\nClick **Let's Begin** to start student responses. Click **Instructor View** to check submission status in the **Submitted / Not Submitted** panel.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-sorting/16.png|Image-Based Sorting result Bar Chart]]\n\nAfter closing responses, check the result screen with **View Result**. On the result screen, the number of Correct / Wrong responses is displayed as a graph.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-sorting/17.png|Text-Based Sorting class start screen]]\n\n### Text-Based\n\nIn the Text-Based layout, group boxes appear on the left and a list of text items appears on the right.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-sorting/19.png|Text-Based Sorting answer reveal screen]]\n\nClick **See Answer** to reveal the correct items that should belong in each group.",
            "[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-sorting/21.png|Image-Based Sorting question on the student screen]]\n\n### Image-Based\n\nGroup boxes such as Animal and Plant are displayed at the top of the screen, and shuffled image cards are displayed at the bottom. Following the **Choose your answer** guide at the lower right, students drag the bottom images into the matching group boxes.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-sorting/24.png|Image-Based Sorting ready-to-submit state]]\n\nWhen all images are placed into group boxes, the **Submit** button becomes active in blue.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-sorting/26.png|Image-Based Sorting answer feedback screen]]\n\nAfter the correct answer is revealed, the correct group classification is displayed.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-sorting/27.png|Text-Based Sorting question on the student screen]]\n\n### Text-Based\n\nGroup boxes are displayed on the left, and a list of text items is displayed on the right. Students drag each item into the appropriate group.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-sorting/28.png|Text-Based Sorting ready-to-submit state]]\n\nWhen all items are classified, the **Submit** button becomes active.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-quiz-sorting/30.png|Text-Based Sorting answer feedback screen]]\n\nWhen the teacher reveals the correct answer, the student screen shows Correct / Wrong feedback together with the correct text classification."
      ]
});
