            "**Traffic Light** is a Discussion Activity where students quickly express their opinion using green, yellow, and red traffic-light colors.\n\nEach color means 🟢 **Agree**, 🟡 **Neutral**, and 🔴 **Disagree**. It is suitable for discussion classes where you need to quickly check positions and collect short opinions.",
            "[[image:edit-lesson-discussion-traffic-light/01.png|Traffic Light editing screen]]\n\n**Screen structure:**\n\n- 🟢 **Agree**: Agree\n\n- 🟡 **Neutral**: Not sure / neutral\n\n- 🔴 **Disagree**: Disagree\n\n- Subtitle text explaining the meaning of each color is displayed together.\n\n**Right panel settings:**\n\n- **Background Color**: Select the background color of the activity screen.\n\n- **3 Second's Countdown**: Set whether to show a countdown before the activity starts.\n\n- **Write comments after voting**: Allows students to write a reason after choosing a color.\n\n- **Bar Chart / Bubble / Lane Chart**: Select how results are displayed.",
            "[[image:edit-lesson-discussion-traffic-light/03.png|Traffic Light class start screen]]\n\nWhen you move to the **Traffic Light** slide on the class screen, the question and three traffic-light buttons are displayed. Click **Let's Begin** at the lower right to start student participation.\n\nWhen students submit their opinions, end the activity with **Finish Up** and check the result screen with **View Result**.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-discussion-traffic-light/07.png|Traffic Light result Bar Chart]]\n\nOn the result screen, the distribution of Agree / Neutral / Disagree responses is displayed as a graph.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-discussion-traffic-light/08.png|Traffic Light opinion card screen]]\n\nClick **See Opinion** to view the opinions of students who selected each color as cards. Use the filters at the top to view only the category you want.",
            "[[image:edit-lesson-discussion-traffic-light/15.png|Traffic Light question on the student screen]]\n\nOn the student screen, the question, image, and three traffic-light buttons (**Agree / Neutral / Disagree**) are displayed.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-discussion-traffic-light/16.png|Student selected Agree screen]]\n\nWhen the student chooses a color, a blue border appears around the selected button, and the **Write Opinion** button becomes active.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-discussion-traffic-light/19.png|Traffic Light opinion writing screen]]\n\nClick **Write Opinion** to display the selected color as a large circular bubble and write an opinion in the input field at the bottom.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-discussion-traffic-light/20.png|Traffic Light screen after opinion submission]]\n\nAfter submitting the opinion, the button becomes inactive to prevent duplicate submissions."
