Object.assign(translations.en.articleBodies, {
      "edit-lesson-discussion-vote": [
            "**Vote** is a Discussion Activity where students vote for one option from several choices and, if needed, write the reason for their choice.\n\nIt supports two layouts: Image-Based and Text-Based. Since it has no right or wrong answer, it is well suited for checking students’ preferences, reasons for selection, and differences in opinion.",
            "[[image:edit-lesson-discussion-vote/01.png|Vote Text-Based editing screen]]\n\nText-Based displays the options as a text list.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-discussion-vote/02.png|Vote Image-Based editing screen]]\n\nImage-Based displays each option as a card with an attached image.\n\n**Screen structure:**\n\n- Click the **×** button on the right side of each option to delete that option.\n\n- Click the **+** button at the bottom to add a new option.\n\n**Right panel settings:**\n\n- **Background Color**: Select the background color of the activity screen.\n\n- **3 Second's Countdown**: Set whether to show a countdown before the activity starts.\n\n- **Write comments after voting**: Allows students to write an opinion after making a choice.\n\n- **Bar Chart / Bubble / Lane Chart**: Select how results are displayed.\n\n- **Time Limit**: Set the activity time limit.\n\n> ⚠️ If the image options are important to the topic, use the **Image-Based** layout so students can make choices more intuitively.",
            "[[image:edit-lesson-discussion-vote/10.png|Image-Based Vote class start screen]]\n\n### Image-Based\n\nWhen you move to the **Vote** slide on the class screen, the question and image option cards are displayed. Click **Let's Begin** at the lower right to start the vote.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-discussion-vote/13.png|Image-Based Vote result Bar Chart]]\n\nAfter closing responses, use **View Result** to check the number of votes for each option.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-discussion-vote/14.png|Image-Based Vote opinion card screen]]\n\nClick **See Opinion** to view student opinions for each option as cards.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-discussion-vote/19.png|Text-Based Vote class start screen]]\n\n### Text-Based\n\nIn the Text-Based layout, options are displayed as a text list instead of images.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-discussion-vote/21.png|Text-Based Vote result Bar Chart]]\n\nOn the result screen, the vote count for each text option is displayed as a graph.",
            "[[image:edit-lesson-discussion-vote/26.png|Image-Based Vote question on the student screen]]\n\n### Image-Based\n\nOn the student screen, the question, related image, and option images are displayed at the bottom. When a student clicks the desired option, it is highlighted with a blue border and the **Write Opinion** button becomes active.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-discussion-vote/27.png|Image-Based Vote opinion writing screen]]\n\nClick **Write Opinion** to display the selected image larger in the center and write the reason for the choice in the input field at the bottom.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-discussion-vote/31.png|Image-Based Vote submission complete screen]]\n\nAfter submitting the opinion, the selected image and written opinion are displayed with the **Your opinion is** message.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-discussion-vote/33.png|Text-Based Vote question on the student screen]]\n\n### Text-Based\n\nWhen a student selects an item from the text option list, a check mark appears and the **Write Opinion** button becomes active.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-discussion-vote/35.png|Text-Based Vote opinion writing screen]]\n\nThe selected item name is displayed large in the center, and the student can write the reason in the input field at the bottom.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-discussion-vote/37.png|Text-Based Vote submission complete screen]]\n\nAfter submission, the selected text item and written opinion are displayed on the result confirmation screen."
      ]
});
