                          "Click the **Self Study** button at the top of the Edit Lesson screen to open the dropdown. Select **Individual**.\n\n- **Individual**: A mode where students solve questions and learn individually.\n\n- **Challenge**: A game-style learning mode that increases participation through competition.\n\n- **Flash Cards**: A mode for repeated learning with flash cards.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-self-study-individual/01.png|Step 1. Select Individual mode]]\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-self-study-individual/02.png|Step 1. Select Individual mode]]\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-self-study-individual/03.png|Step 1. Select Individual mode]]",
                          "Configure the assignment details in the **Individual** popup.\n\n### Assignment Name\n\nThe current Lesson name is shown as the default. Click **Edit** to switch to a text field where you can enter the assignment name directly. After editing, click **Save** or cancel with **Cancel**.\n\n### Settings\n\n- **Due Date**: Turn on the toggle to set a due date and time. Set the date with the calendar and the time with the dropdown.\n\n- **Time Limit**: Turn on the toggle to set a time limit. Enter the limit in minutes, up to **100 minutes**.\n\n- **Check correctness for each question**: Lets students check whether each answer is correct immediately after answering. The default value is ON.\n\n### Access Level\n\n- **Public link (Guest access)**: Anyone who knows the link or Access Code can participate.\n\n- **Class Only (Private access)**: Only students assigned to a specific Class can participate. When selected, you move to a screen where you set Year / School / Grade / **Class Name (Required)**.\n\nAfter completing the settings, click **Assign**.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-self-study-individual/04.png|Step 2. Configure the assignment]]\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-self-study-individual/05.png|Step 2. Configure the assignment]]\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-self-study-individual/06.png|Step 2. Configure the assignment]]",
                          "After clicking **Assign**, the **Share Assignment** screen appears. There are three ways to share the assignment with students.\n\n- **URL**: Copy and share the assignment link directly. Use **Copy Link** to copy it to the clipboard.\n\n- **QR Code**: Click **QR Code** to generate a QR code. Students can scan it with a smartphone and open the assignment directly. (\"Scan to open assignment\")\n\n- **Access Code**: Give students the numeric code, such as 5318, so they can join by entering the code after accessing LumiTeach.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-self-study-individual/07.png|Step 3. Share the assignment]]\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-self-study-individual/08.png|Step 3. Share the assignment]]"
