                          "Configure the assignment details in the **Flash Cards** popup.\n\n### Assignment Name\n\nClick **Edit** to switch to a text field where you can enter the assignment name. After editing, click **Save** or cancel with **Cancel**.\n\n### Settings\n\n- **Due Date**: Turn on the toggle to set a due date and time.\n\n- **Time Limit**: Turn on the toggle to set a time limit. Enter the limit in minutes, up to **100 minutes**.\n\n> Flash Cards mode does not provide the answer checking option (**Check correctness**) or leaderboard option (**Show Leaderboard**). It is optimized for students to learn on their own by repeatedly reviewing cards.\n\n### Access Level\n\n- **Public link (Guest access)**: Anyone who knows the link or Access Code can participate.\n\n- **Class Only (Private access)**: Only students assigned to a specific Class can participate.\n\nAfter completing the settings, click **Assign**.\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-self-study-flash-card/03.png|Step 2. Configure the assignment]]\n\n[[image:edit-lesson-self-study-flash-card/04.png|Step 2. Configure the assignment]]",
