                          "[[image:toolkit-bell/01.png|Tool Kit list with Bell selected]]\n\nClick the **+** button in the tool bar at the bottom of the class screen to open the **All Tools** list. Select **Bell** in the **Normal** category to run the alert bell tool.\n\nBell can be used to get students' attention or signal a transition between activities.",
                          "[[image:toolkit-bell/03.png|Bell message input screen]]\n\nYou can enter a message to show students in the input field above the bell icon (\"Type the message for students (optional)\"). The message is optional, so you can ring the bell even if you leave it blank.\n\nFor example, if you enter a short instruction such as **Everybody Focus !!**, that message appears together when the bell rings.",
                          "[[image:toolkit-bell/05.png|Bell ringing screen with Stop button]]\n\nClick **Ring** to make the bell swing side to side and play the bell sound. If you entered a message, the message appears at the top of the screen so students can immediately see what they should do.\n\nWhile the bell is ringing, the button changes to **Stop**.",
                          "Click **Stop** to stop the bell sound. If you need to continue explaining right after getting attention during class, ring it only as long as needed and end it with Stop.\n\nIf you need another alert, keep the message as it is and click **Ring** again."
