                          "[[image:toolkit-annotate/01.png|Annotate writing screen with basic toolbar]]\n\nEnter content in the title area and body text. For example, if you enter **Hello EveryOne**, it appears in large text on the student screen.\n\nYou can enter up to **10,000 characters**, and the current character count is shown at the bottom right of the screen. Use the bottom toolbar to adjust the font size and basic formatting.\n\n- **Font size**: Select the font size from the dropdown.\n\n- **B / I / U**: Apply bold, italic, or underline.\n\n- **A icon**: Increase or decrease the font size.\n\n- **+**: Add a new note.",
                          "[[image:toolkit-annotate/02.png|Annotate background color selection screen]]\n\nClick the fill icon to open the **Color** picker. You can choose a color from the color area or enter a color value directly in the input field at the bottom.\n\nChanging the background color changes the overall mood of the note screen, so use it when you want an attention-grabbing phrase or activity instruction to stand out more clearly.",
                          "[[image:toolkit-annotate/04.png|Annotation List saved notes screen]]\n\nUse the save-related buttons at the bottom to keep notes or load them again later.\n\n- **Auto-Save**: When enabled, your writing is saved automatically.\n\n- **Save**: Save the current note.\n\n- **Print**: Print the note.\n\n- **List**: Open **Annotation List**, the list of saved notes. The list shows the number of saved notes, the creation time, and each note title.\n\nYou can manage up to **50 saved notes**. Delete individual notes with the **X** button, or delete all notes with **Delete All**."
