                {
                          "title": "8. Quick Quiz",
                          "desc": "Quick Quiz is a tool for creating a quiz on the spot during class and presenting it to students. It supports two types: Multiple Choice and Short Answer.",
                          "note": "Click the tool icon in Tool Kit at the bottom of the class screen to run it.",
                          "sections": [
                                    "How to run",
                                    "Select the quiz type",
                                    "Create Multiple Choice",
                                    "Display and reveal the answer",
                                    "Check results"
                          ]
                },
                [
                          "[[image:toolkit-quick-quiz/01.png|Quick Quiz initial creation screen]]\n\nClick the **Quick Quiz** icon in the toolbar at the bottom of the class screen to open the instant quiz creation window. Quick Quiz is a tool used to quickly check student understanding during class or to give a short check question in the middle of an activity.\n\nAt the top, you can select either **Multiple Choice** or **Short Answer**. The default screen opens in the Multiple Choice creation state, and the right panel lets you check student response results and Live Q&A later.",
                          "[[image:toolkit-quick-quiz/02.png|Completed Quick Quiz Multiple Choice creation screen]]\n\nIn **Multiple Choice**, enter the question in the top input field and write the options in the option fields below. Select the checkbox to the left of each option to set that option as the answer.\n\n- Use the **+** button to add options.\n\n- You can set up to **5** options.\n\n- Use the **X** button to the right of each option to delete options you do not need.\n\nAfter preparing the question, options, and answer, click the **Display** button to show the quiz on student screens.",
                          "[[image:toolkit-quick-quiz/04.png|Quick Quiz empty option error notice]]\n\nIf you click **Display** after adding an option but leaving its content empty, the **Some options are empty.** notice appears.\n\nIn this case, fill in all empty options, or delete unused options with the **X** button, then click Display again. Since the error appears before the quiz is presented to students, it is helpful to check first whether any options are empty or whether an answer is missing.",
                          "[[image:toolkit-quick-quiz/06.png|Quick Quiz displayed on the student screen]]\n\nWhen the quiz is presented, the student screen shows the question and numbered options. In a multiple-choice quiz, students can select one of the options to respond.\n\nThe teacher screen shows the **Show Answer** button, and after receiving student responses, the teacher can reveal the answer.",
                          "[[image:toolkit-quick-quiz/08.png|Quick Quiz answer reveal screen]]\n\nWhen you click **Show Answer**, the option set as the answer is highlighted, and a celebration effect appears on the screen. In this state, students can immediately check the correct answer.\n\nIn the **Activity Results** tab on the right panel, you can check student response results, and in the **Live Q&A** tab, you can check real-time questions."
                ]
