        "[[image:setting-curriculum/01.png|Curriculum default screen]]\n\n[[callout:i||The instructions below use NGSS as an example to explain how to use Curriculum.\\nThe details shown in Curriculum Tree and Curriculum Details may vary depending on the registered Curriculum.]]\n\n### Open Curriculum\n\nClick **Curriculum** in the top navigation to open the curriculum page.\n\n### Screen layout\n\nAt the top of the page, the name and description of the currently selected curriculum are displayed. For example, when **NGSS (Next Generation Science Standards)** is selected, the description of that standard and the total number of content items (**Total**) are shown together.\n\n### Curriculum Tree (left panel)\n\nUse the **Curriculum Tree** on the left to browse content by grade and domain.\n\nUse the top dropdown, such as **grade All**, to filter by grade.\n\nThe tree expands in the order of school level (**Elementary School**) → grade (**Grade K ~ Grade 3 …**) → domain. For example, under **Grade K**, the domains **PS (Physical Science)**, **LS (Life Science)**, **ESS (Earth and Space Science)**, and **ETS (Engineering, Technology, and Applications of Science)** are shown.\n\n### Lesson / Assessment tabs\n\nIn the right area, switch between the **Lesson** and **Assessment** tabs.\n\n**Lesson**: Lesson cards grouped by topic or cluster are displayed, such as **Forces and Interactions: Pushes and Pulls** and **Engineering Design**. Each card shows the number of activities (**N Activities**) and the subject.",
        "[[image:setting-curriculum/02.png|Select Curriculum window]]\n\n### Change Curriculum\n\nClick **Change Curriculum** at the top to open the **Select Curriculum** window. Select the curriculum you want, then click **Apply** to apply it. Examples of selectable curricula include:\n\n- **NGSS (Next Generation Science Standards)**\n- **CCSS (Common Core State Standards for Mathematics)**\n- Other registered curricula",
